Update CONTRIBUTING.md

Made some revisions in reference to PR 21, adding info about Transitland
Minor Spelling and Sentence Completion Revisions
Updated Submitting and Requesting Changes

Update Resources on Contributing Doc

Now that the project has extended its visibility, it's time to update some of the items appearing on this page to welcome new contributors. This is a very remedial first step in accomplishing this.

Merge pull request #16 from AcademyInPeril/master

Slight copy revisions
Cleaned up CONTRIBUTORS.md

Updated repo link in CONTRIBUTING.md

Updated repo link to reflect the ownership change from Robert to Viktor

Made location code only run on homepage
Should fix Issue #15
Updated geolocation error handling to print non user errors
Fixed incorrect scale on stop coordinates
Trying to fix search being invalid with MySQL
Fixed decimal format not working on production
Increased location range to 0.5 miles

Moved back to .delete_all for initial cleaning
This is because otherwise the lines_stops table is not cleared

Heavily optimized create_transit rake task
This was done by making it only use five queries. First two for storing initial Lines and Stops (after pairing), second two to read them back, and last query to make the lines_stops associations

Heavily optimized rake task DB actions
By using activerecord-import, one DB query is made for creating lines, and one for stops. This cut down the query time from a few minutes to a few seconds
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/vkoves/Transit-Network

Added metrics for objects made to rake task
This will show how many lines and stops were in the data set

Added time benchmarking to setup_transit
This should help when making optimizations to the task

Updated Readme to link to new Travis CI page

As with the Travis CI image source change earlier, caused due to transfer of ownership.

Switched to delete_all for optimization
In Ruby delete_all does not fire callbacks, making it much faster than destroy_all
Removed duplicate GTFS section from README
Updated README with links to core files
Updated README With Improved GTFS Setup

Fixed Travis CI Build Status Image

Caused by repository ownership transfer
